        "timestamp": "2018-04-26 12:36:31.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI referred other project health checks (for example aai) its written as below, where the namespace is referred using the .Values.nsPrefix and i checked in the jenkins, the Health check for AAI is PASS. so should i revert my patch to match this service health check.\nThanks. \n{\n  \"service\": {\n    \"name\": \"Active and Available Inventory\",\n    \"checks\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"aai-service\",\n        \"name\": \"Core A&AI\",\n        \"http\": \"https://aai-service.{{ .Values.nsPrefix }}:8443/aai/util/echo\",\n        \"header\": {\n          \"Authorization\": [\"Basic QUFJOkFBSQ==\"],\n          \"X-TransactionId\": [\"ConsulHealthCheck\"],\n          \"X-FromAppId\": [\"healthcheck\"]\n        },\n        \"tls_skip_verify\": true,\n        \"interval\": \"15s\",\n        \"timeout\": \"1s\"\n      },\n      {\n\n\nbtw, i tried and double quote is not required from the current patch.",
        "patchset_number": 2
